Privacy Policy
Effective Date: 1 June 2025

1. Introduction
Reytec Solutions B.V. (“Reytec”, “we”, “us”, or “our”) respects your privacy and is committed to protecting your personal data. This privacy policy explains how we collect, use, and safeguard your information when you visit our website, use our services, or otherwise interact with us.

2. Who We Are
Reytec Solutions B.V. is a private limited company registered in the Netherlands. We offer professional and technology services including [describe core offerings, e.g., software development, IT consultancy, etc.].

3. What Data We Collect
We may collect and process the following categories of personal data:
	•	Contact Information: Name, email address, phone number, company name, and role
	•	Technical Data: IP address, browser type, operating system, usage data through cookies and analytics tools
	•	Communication Data: Records of correspondence with us (emails, chats, etc.)
	•	Customer Data: Information provided by our clients in the context of service delivery (may include personal data depending on the nature of the service)

4. How We Collect Data
We collect personal data through:
	•	Our website contact forms
	•	Direct communication (e.g., email, phone, events)
	•	Service engagement and onboarding
	•	Automated technologies (cookies, analytics)

5. How We Use Your Data
We use your personal data for the following purposes:
	•	To communicate with you and respond to inquiries
	•	To provide and manage our services
	•	To maintain and improve our website and platforms
	•	For legal and contractual obligations
	•	To send updates or newsletters (only with consent)

6. Legal Basis for Processing
We process your data based on one or more of the following grounds:
	•	Your consent (Article 6(1)(a) GDPR)
	•	Performance of a contract (Article 6(1)(b))
	•	Compliance with legal obligations (Article 6(1)(c))
	•	Legitimate interests (Article 6(1)(f)) such as business development and service improvement

7. Data Sharing
We do not sell your data. We may share your personal data with:
	•	Service providers and processors who assist in our operations (e.g., hosting, CRM tools)
	•	Legal or regulatory authorities if required by law
	•	Affiliates or subsidiaries under Reytec Holdings, if applicable

8. International Transfers
If we transfer data outside the EEA, we ensure appropriate safeguards are in place (e.g., Standard Contractual Clauses).

9. Data Retention
We retain personal data only as long as necessary for the purposes described or as required by law. Contact data is typically retained for 2 years unless you request earlier deletion.

10. Your Rights
Under GDPR, you have the right to:
	•	Access your personal data
	•	Request correction or deletion
	•	Object to processing or request restriction
	•	Data portability
	•	Withdraw consent at any time
To exercise these rights, email us at [hello@reytec.solutions] (or your actual contact email).

11. Cookies
We use cookies for functionality and analytics. You can control cookie settings through your browser. For more details, see our [Cookie Policy].

12. Security
We implement appropriate technical and organizational measures to secure your data against loss, misuse, or unauthorized access.

13. Changes to This Policy
We may update this policy from time to time. The latest version will always be available on our website.

14. Contact
For any questions or concerns regarding this policy or your data, please contact us:

Reytec Solutions B.V.
Email: [helloy@reytec.solutions]
